area_name: Boulder B aka Two Cylinder Boulder

content.description: Start low and climb up the South Face.
content.location:
B is the second boulder you come to going up the road. Looking at the group of three boulders from the road, this is the one on the left. It is called Two Cylinder Boulder in the

Colorado Bouldering

book.

This is the route just left of the SE arete.

content.description: Start low on the left side of the North face of the boulder.
content.location:
B is the second boulder you come to going up the road. Looking at the group of three boulders from the road, this is the one on the left. It is called Two Cylinder Boulder in the Colorado Bouldering book.

It is on the left side of the back (North side) of the boulder.

content.description: Climb the arete on the Southeast Side.
content.location:

This climbs the Southeast arete.
